  "texts": [
    "Definition 6.11 (Second-Order Translation).",
    "For each first-order variable x, define the second-order translation SOT x: L(Φ, I) → L 2 (Φ, I) as follows, where Q is a second-order variable:1.",
    "RO( Q) = ∀v( Qv ↔ ∀v ′ (v ′ ⊑ v → ∃v ′′ (v ′′ ⊑ v ′ ∧ Qv ′′))); 2.",
    "SOT x (φ) = ∀ Q1... ∀ Qn (( 1≤i≤n RO( Qi)) → ST x (φ)),where Q1,..., Qn are the unary predicates occurring in ST x (φ).Let SOT (φ) = ∀xSOT x (φ).",
    "◁From now on we will drop the dots over symbols when we trust there is no danger of confusion, and we will use abbreviations of the form '∀y ⊑ x' for restricted quantification."
  ],
